“With the support of the UK government, donors, national governments and Global Citizen members like you, we can make the social injustice of malnutrition a thing of the past,” said Tracey Ullman, Power of Nutrition Ambassador, at a live concert in London in April 2018.
The group also said that after implementing more than 5,000 actions calling on the UK to improve the quality of nutrition for mothers and children, the government has announced funding for the Power of Nutrition project, which will reach 5 million women and children with nutritional problems.
One of the most frequently asked questions on their website was “How do you know you can eradicate extreme poverty?”
Global Citizen responded: “It will be a long and difficult road —sometimes we will stumble and fail.
