Federal prosecutors demand death penalty for suspected terrorist attack in New York
Federal prosecutors from New York demand the death penalty for Sayfull Saipov suspected of carrying out a terrorist attack in New York, which killed eight people. This is a rare punishment — it was not executed in this state for a federal crime since 1953.
